        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 7:21PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 720 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 18
miles west of Hardin, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hardin.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
